Proposed timetable:
# TravelPlan: La Palma Dark Sky Astronomy Trip — Hamburg to La Palma, 12–19 Nov 2026

| Day 1 — 2026-11-12 — Arrival: Hamburg to La Palma, transfer to Garafía | Day 2 — 2026-11-13 — Garafía orientation and first guided stargazing | Day 3 — 2026-11-14 — GR-131 high-ridge hiking and independent dark-sky session | Day 4 — 2026-11-15 — Roque de los Muchachos Visitor Centre and observatory landscape | Day 5 — 2026-11-16 — Caldera de Taburiente hiking day | Day 6 — 2026-11-17 — Llano del Jable astronomical viewpoint night | Day 7 — 2026-11-18 — Flexible weather buffer and Garafía local day | Day 8 — 2026-11-19 — Departure: Garafía to SPC, fly to Hamburg |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **1. Flight day: Hamburg (HAM) to La Palma (SPC)** [transport] 08:00–18:00 @ Hamburg Airport to La Palma Airport (€530.00) — Round-trip flight search returned no selectable carrier/timetable yet for Nov 2026, but Google Flights price insight shows a typical HAM–SPC return range of about €310–€750. Hold this as the travel window and verify/book when schedules open. — Links: [link 1](https://www.google.com/travel/flights?hl=en&gl=us&curr=EUR&tfs=CBwQAhoeEgoyMDI2LTExLTEyagcIARIDSEFNcgcIARIDU1BDGh4SCjIwMjYtMTEtMTlqBwgBEgNTUENyBwgBEgNIQU1AAUgBcAGYAQE&tfu=EgIIAQ) | **1. Breakfast at lodging** [meal] 08:30–09:15 @ Pension Roque Faro / Garafía (€8.00) — Slow breakfast and weather check before local orientation. | **1. Breakfast and pack hiking kit** [meal] 07:30–08:15 @ Pension Roque Faro (€8.00) — Prepare water, sun protection, wind layer, snacks, offline maps, and warm summit clothing. | **1. Breakfast at lodging** [meal] 07:30–08:15 @ Pension Roque Faro (€8.00) — Early breakfast before the observatory visit; bring warm layers for the 2,300m altitude. | **1. Breakfast and Caldera hiking safety check** [meal] 07:00–07:45 @ Pension Roque Faro (€8.00) — Early breakfast, pack 2L+ water, lunch, rain shell, sun protection, and offline maps for Caldera de Taburiente. | **1. Late breakfast after hiking recovery** [meal] 09:00–09:45 @ Pension Roque Faro (€8.00) — Easy morning after the Caldera day and before an evening observing session. | **1. Breakfast and weather decision point** [meal] 08:30–09:15 @ Pension Roque Faro (€8.00) — Use the final full day as a flexible buffer: if a previous stargazing or observatory plan was clouded/windy, move it here. | **1. Breakfast and check out** [meal] 07:30–08:30 @ Pension Roque Faro, Garafía (€8.00) — Final breakfast, room check, and checkout from the Garafía dark-sky base. |
